===Origin===
====Aeneas and the Forgotten One====
Circa the 11th century, [[Aeneas (Earth-616)|Aeneas]],{{r|Marvel Atlas #1|; [[Italy]]'s entry}} a survivor of the [[Trojan War]],{{r|Thor Annual #8}} and his men, including the [[Eternals (Homo immortalis)|Eternal]] [[Gilgamesh (Earth-616)|"Hero"]] conquered [[Latium]],{{r|Marvel Atlas #1|; [[Italy]]'s entry}} and united the Etruscan tribes that would one day found Rome.{{r|Official Handbook of the Marvel Universe A to Z Vol 1 8}}

Etruscan and Greek influence waxed and waned from the 9th to 5th centuries BC, Rome became dominant thereafter, unifying the peninsula by conquest and colonization.{{r|Marvel Atlas #1|; [[Italy]]'s entry}}

====Romulus and Remus====
[[Romulus (Earth-616)|Romulus]] and [[Remus (Earth-616)|Remus]] were adopted by a female [[Wolves|wolf]], and came to found [[Rome (Italy)|Rome]],{{r|New Mutants #9}}{{r|New Mutants #10}} which was founded in 625 BC.{{r|Wolverine Vol 3 53}}

===200 B.C.===
Around 200 B.C., the [[Robe (Earth-616)|Robe of Evil]] fell into the hands of a brutal tyrant named [[Peragmum (Earth-616)|Peragmum the Ruthless]] until he was killed.{{r|Captain America Comics #53}}

In the 2nd and 1st centuries BC, Rome absorbed [[Greece]], introducing the worship of the [[Olympians|Olympian gods]] among the Romans, under different names.{{r|Marvel Atlas #1|; [[Italy]]'s entry}}

===100 B.C.===
In 64 B.C. the [[Eternals (Homo immortalis)|Eternal]]; [[Sersi (Earth-616)|Sersi]] befriended [[Lucius Sergius Catilina (Earth-616)|Lucius Sergius Catilina]], who with the help of a group aristocrats attempted to overthrow consulship of [[Marcus Tullius Cicero (Earth-616)|Marcus Tullius Cicero]]. Cicero exposed the conspiracy and forced Catilina to flee Rome.{{r|Eternals Vol 5 2}}

===Caesar, Crassus and Pompey===
By 59 B.C., [[Julius Caesar (Earth-616)|Julius Caesar]] was among the most popular men in Rome. As a veteran to many successful campaigns that had contributed to extend the influence of Rome through Northern [[Europe]], he was elected by the [[Centuriate Assembly (Earth-616)|Centuriate Assembly]] as "Senior Consul of the Roman Republic".<!-- {{r|Civil War: Front Line #2|; unnamed story}} --><!-- {{r|Marvel Atlas #1|; [[Italy]]'s entry}} on the part of spreading Roman Republic influence across Europe --> He shared the Consulate position with both [[Pompey (Earth-616)|Pompey the Great]] and millionaire [[Marcus Licinius Crassus (Earth-616)|Marcus Licinius Crassus]]. Despite his obvious benefit to Rome, Caesar's moves were often blocked by the corrupt [[Roman Senate (Earth-616)|Roman Senate]].{{r|Civil War: Front Line #2|; unnamed story}} 

Around 57 B.C., Caesar led the Roman armies and conquered the [[Belgium|northern part of Gaul]], fighting its inhabitants, a mixture of [[Germanic]] and [[Celtic]] tribes, the [[Belgae]], whom he described as the bravest of the Gauls.{{r|Marvel Atlas #1|; [[Belgium]]'s entry}} By 55 B.C., Caesar's first Roman expedition arrived in [[Britannia]],{{r|Marvel Atlas #1|; [[United Kingdom]]'s entry}} where he fought the [[Celts]] who didn't unite against him.{{r|Savage Sword of Conan #42|; Kings of the Night}}

The same year, [[Harley Davis (Earth-616)|Harley Davis]] and [[Julius Mullarkey (Earth-616)|Killpower]] were accidentally sent back in time to ancient Rome and landed a [[Colosseum (Rome)|Colosseum]] with gladiator battling lions. Their apparition scared the lions, who nearly killed Julius Caesar. Harley used her sonic cry to knocking the lion aside. They then escape back to the future.{{r|Motormouth & Killpower #9}}<!-- Emperor's game: error ? -->

Playing one tribe against another, Caesar eventually conquered all of Gaul{{r|Savage Sword of Conan #42|; Kings of the Night}} by 52 B.C.{{r|Marvel Atlas #1|; [[France]]'s entry}}

[[File:Crossing the Rubicon from Civil War Front Line Vol 1 2 0001.png|thumb|300px|right|[[Julius Caesar (Earth-616)|Caesar]] [[Crossing the Rubicon|crossing]] the [[Rubicon (River)|Rubicon]]]]
====Crossing the Rubicon====
In 50 B.C., Caesar was ordered by the Senate to disband his legions and return to Rome.<!-- {{r|Civil War: Front Line #2|; unnamed story}} --> Caesar saw that demand as an illegal act, as his consulship was legitimate and yet he was forbidden to stand for a second term. On January 10th in the year 49 B.C., accused of insubordination and treason, he brought his single legion to the [[Rubicon (River)|Rubicon]], the natural border marking the edge of his territory and parting [[Gaul]] from the rest of [[Italy]]. Despite unwilling to fight, Caesar refused to back down, refusing to die in Rome. There, he stated ''Alea Iacta Est'' (''"the die is already cast"''), and [[Crossing the Rubicon|crossed]] the Rubicon, engaging the defenders of Rome and defeating them, expecting to reach Rome by the end of the week.{{r|Civil War: Front Line #2|; unnamed story}}

===Julius Caesar's rule===
Caesar became Dictator,{{r|Marvel Atlas #1|; [[Italy]]'s entry}} while being usually thought of as Emperor.{{r|Fantastic Four Vol 4 5}}

====Egypt Civil War====
Circa 47-49 B.C., a civil war erupted in Egypt as Caesar attempted to put [[Cleopatra (Earth-616)|Cleopatra]] on the throne in place of her brother [[Ptolemy XIII Theos Philopator (Earth-616)|Ptolemy]] (supported by [[Zota of Pergamum (Earth-616)|Zota of Pergamum]]). During the siege of the palace by the Egyptians led by Ptolemy, Caesar and Cleopatra were approached by [[Stephen Strange (Earth-616)|Doctor Strange]] and [[Clea (Earth-616)|Clea]]. It was told that it was during that event that the [[Great Library of Alexandria|Great Library]] of [[Alexandria]] was burned down, though it was in fact (as [[Marcus Annaeus Lucanus (Earth-616)|Lucan]] would later wrote) warehouses in which grain and books were stored that were burned due to a defensive fire set by Caesar's troops near the docks. Nevertheless, the theory of Caesar burning the Library became a popular legend,{{r|Doctor Strange, Sorcerer Supreme #33}} and is still mentioned.{{r|Fall of the Hulks: Alpha #1}}

====Secret death and replacement====
During the [[Battle of Thapsus]]<!-- 46 B.C. on [[Earth-1218]] -->, Caesar's [[Legio V Alaudae (Earth-616)|Fifth Legion]] repelled a charge of Elephants of War. At that time, an [[Charles Cotta (Earth-616)|alien observer]] had came witness his life. After the battle, Caesar would commemorate the event by creating a coin featuring the pachyderms. Caesar would have an accident while riding an elephant who was frightened by a serpent, resulting in his death before his appointed time. The alien feared that is was his presence who had altered the timeline, and so decided that in order to prevent a time paradox, it would continue Caesar's destiny by taking possession of Caesar's body, until his assassination in 44 B.C.{{r|Fantastic Four Vol 4 5}}

===="Death"====
In 44 B.C., "Julius Caesar" was assassinated on the Ides of March by [[Marcus Brutus (Earth-616)|Marcus Brutus]] and the Senators.{{r|Fantastic Four Vol 4 5}} The immortal [[Neanderthal]] [[Cole (Neanderthal) (Earth-616)|Cole]]{{r|Cable #96}} and the immortal [[Maha Yogi (Earth-616)|Maha Yogi]] witnessed this event,{{r|Incredible Hulk #210}} while the [[Fantastic Four (Earth-616)|Fantastic Four]] were involved in helping the Caesar impersonator.{{r|Fantastic Four Vol 4 5}}

===Civil War===
They hoped to bring back the republic, but civil war broke out instead.{{r|Incredible Hulk #210}} Caesar's foster son [[Gaius Octavius (Earth-616)|Augustus]] battled for control of Rome.{{r|Marvel Atlas #1|; [[Italy]]'s entry}}

===Augustus' rule===
Augustus proclaimed himself Rome's first emperor in 27 B.C.{{r|Marvel Atlas #1|; [[Italy]]'s entry}}

After [[Charles Cotta (Earth-616)|"Julius Caesar"]]'s "assassination", Augustus battled for control of Rome, and proclaimed himself Rome's first emperor in 27 B.C.{{r|Marvel Atlas #1|; [[Italy]]'s entry}}

In 41 BC, [[Marc Antony (Earth-616)|Marc Antony]], one of the triumvirs, was given the Eastern sphere of the Roman Empire to rule. There, he met and fell in love with [[Cleopatra (Earth-616)|Cleopatra]], the Queen of [[Egypt]], who was also a consort of Julius Caesar during his life. Despite marrying Octavius's sister [[Octavia (Earth-616)|Octavia]], Antony continued to lust after Cleopatra. This lead to war with Octavius, which Antony lost, in part because Cleopatra withdrew her fleet at a crucial moment. Aware that Antony was furious with her, Cleopatra sent him false news that she has killed herself because of him. Thus convinced of her love, Antony fell on his sword to join her in death. Upon hearing of this, Cleopatra committed suicide by allowing herself to be bitten by a poisonous asp.{{r|Ideal #1}}

In 1 BC, Augustus decreed that a census be taken, and every person in the entire Roman Empire had to go to his own town to register. A young couple from [[Nazareth]], [[Joseph of Nazareth (Earth-616)|Joseph]], being of the line of [[David (Earth-616)|King David]], was required to go to [[Bethlehem]] to register with his wife [[Mary of Nazareth (Earth-616)|Mary]]. While in Bethlehem, Mary gave birth to a son named [[Jesus of Nazareth (Earth-616)|Jesus Christ]] the son of the [[Yahweh (Earth-616)|God]] of the [[Israelites]]. his teaching would change the world for centuries to come.{{r|Life of Christ #1}}

===A.D.<!-- will be replaced by the relevant emperor(s)'s sectio -->===

===Tiberius' rule===
[[Tiberius Caesar Augustus (Earth-616)|Tiberius]] was the second Roman Emperor, reigning from 14 to 37 A.D.. He succeeded his stepfather, Augustus. The [[Eternals (Homo immortalis)|Eternal]]; [[Khoryphos (Earth-616)|Khoryphos]] was working on a monumental musical composition since the reign of Tiberius.{{r|Eternals Vol 2 5}} 

In 25 A.D., a man from the 20th century traveled back in time to the Roman Empire and set himself up as king, but all the present day devices he had brought back with him to prove his claims do not work without electricity, fuel, and broadcasting stations.{{r|Tales of Suspense #21|; The Man From... Tomorrow!}}

In 30, A.D., Jesus Christ's visited the city [[Jerusalem]] during "Passover" which would later be known as the "Last Supper". Jesus told his followers that one of them would betray him. On Friday, Roman soldiers arrested and tried Jesus and nailed him to a cross. When Jesus died, his friends placed his body in a cave and covered the cave entrance with a rock. On Sunday, a friend of Jesus named Mary Magdalene went to the cave. The rock had been rolled away and the cave was empty an [[Angels (Monotheism)|angel]] appeared and said Peace be with you. Jesus is risen from the dead. He then visited his disciples himself to tell them to spread the word of god throughout the world begin Christianity.{{r|Life of Christ: The Easter Story #1}} After his death and as his followers grew in number objects related to him became highly sort after such as the [[Spear of Destiny]] which supposedly the spear a Roman soldier used to kill Jesus{{r|Wolverine: Evilution #1}} and the [[Holy Grail]], supposedly a cup in which Jesus turned water into wine at the Last Supper.{{r|Union Jack #1|3}}

===Caligula's rule===
In 32 A.D., [[Caligula (Earth-616)|Caligula]] became Emperor of Rome. He sent troops to conquer the deepest region of [[Africa]],{{r|Fantastic Four #241}} [[Wakanda]], but the [[Black Panther]] and the Wakandans would beat them back using deadly force each time.{{r|Fantastic Four #608}} [[Flavius Scollio (Earth-616)|Flavius Scollio]] was sent by his commander to investigate an anomalous phenomena, which he discovered was a crashed alien spacecraft. The craft was inhabited by a single alien, which Flavius killed. He then donned the armor which imbued him with power to mentally manipulate his surroundings and advanced longevity. Using the armor, Flavius created the [[Black Tower of M'Kumbe]] in [[Wakanda]], which housed a kingdom modeled after ancient Rome inside, where he resided for centuries.{{r|Fantastic Four #241}}

In 43 AD, the Romans invaded the British Isles.{{r|Marvel Atlas #1|; [[United Kingdom]]'s entry}}

[[File:Clan Akkaba (Earth-616) from X-Men Apocalypse vs. Dracula Vol 1 1 002.jpg|right|250px|thumb]]
===Nero's rule===
In 54 A.D., [[Lucius Domitius Ahenobarbus (Earth-616)|Nero]] became Emperor of Rome. It was during his reign that the 20th century time traveler [[Thomas Tyme (Earth-616)|Tommy Tyme]] and was forced to battle in the gladiator pits. He survived and Nero ordered his execution by lion. Tommy held off the lions with is slingshot before returning to his own era.{{r|Mystic Comics Vol 2 1}}{{citation}}{{Verify source}}<!-- datation, historical events, names of historical places and peoples --> Tommy returned again to an unspecified year to learn more about Roman sportsmanship.{{r|Young Allies #14}}

In 64 A.D.{{citation}}, Nero set fire to Rome and blamed the Christians for it.{{citation}} At some point, agents of the [[Clan Akkaba (Earth-616)|Clan Akkaba]], and it was said that Clan Akkaba was there to ''"light the flame"'' when Rome burned.{{r|X-Men: Apocalypse vs. Dracula #1}} [[Sersi (Earth-616)|Sersi]] was present during Nero's burning of Rome and was assisted by [[Makkari (Earth-616)|Makkari]].{{r|Eternals #4}}

[[File:Romulus (Earth-616) from Wolverine Vol 3 53 0001.jpg|thumb|left]]
In 71 A.D., The [[Colosseum (Rome)|Colosseum]] was built.{{r|Wolverine Vol 3 53}}

In 79 A.D., [[Eruption of Mount Vesuvius in 79 AD|Mount Vesuvius erupted]], destroying the city of [[Pompeii]].{{r|Doctor Doom and the Masters of Evil #4}}

The same year, all the south of the British Isles was under Roman control. Fortifications such as [[Hadrian's Wall]] would be erected to keep the barbarians in the north from raiding the south.{{r|Marvel Atlas #1|; [[United Kingdom]]'s entry}}

During the 1st century Roman historian; [[Publius Cornelius Tacitus (Earth-616)|Tacitus]] told the tales at the beginning of the Christian era and about the region of central Europe was inhabited by the bloodthirsty [[Franks]].{{r|Doctor Strange, Sorcerer Supreme Vol 1 37}} 

