===Trajan's rule===
[[Marcus Ulpius Nerva Traianus (Earth-616)|Marcus Ulpius Nerva Traianus, known as Emperor Trajan]] conquered [[Aqiria]] in approximately 110 AD, incorporating it into the [[Roman Empire]].{{r|Marvel Atlas #2|; [[Aqiria]]'s entry}}

===2nd Century===
<!-- to be completed -->[[Bran Mak Morn (Earth-616)|Bran Mak Morn]], a Pict king rebelled against the Romans after having been forced to watch one of his people being crucified.{{r|Savage Sword of Conan #16}}

Sometime after 176 AD, The [[Eternals (Homo immortalis)|Eternal]]; [[Legba (Eternal) (Earth-616)|Legba]] lived in Rome during the rule of [[Commodus (Earth-616)|Commodus]]. The Emperor told him during an orgy that he was a Sybarite, a person who is self-indulgent in their fondness for sensuous luxury, which he wholeheartedly agreed with the sentiment.{{r|Eternals Annual Vol 4 1}}

At some point the immortal [[Selene Gallio (Earth-616)|Selene Gallio]] had an eye on Senator [[Eliphas (Earth-616)|Eliphas]], who was used by others for their own benefit. She came before him, offering him her eternal love and immortality - if he helped her sacrifice the countless souls of Rome. The thousands of souls that she would feed on would allow her to become as powerful as a god. She instructed her pawn to draw symbols around the city in his own blood for the ritual. However, Eliphas performed a small act of compassion by telling a slave girl he gave ruby earrings to about what was going to happen. Her father informed the authorities, who captured both Eliphas and Selene and sentenced them to be burned at the stake. Selene awoke before it could happen and set the flames back against their would-be executioners. Furious at Eliphas for seemingly betraying her, she took his life-force and transformed him into a vampire-like creature, swearing that he would never see her again.{{r|X-Force Vol 3 11}}

===3rd Century===
In 281 A.D., upon starving to death, [[Decimus Furius (Earth-616)|Decimus Furius]]' [[Homo superior|mutant]] powers emerged. He was consequently attacked and killed dozens before being imprisoned. After years of imprisonment, he was sent to the Colosseum as a gladiator and battled everyday for the next few years of his life for his survival and eventual freedom, and became worshiped as being the dark god '''[[Asterius (Earth-616)|Minotaur]]'''. Decimus was watched by the eternal mutant [[En Sabah Nur (Earth-616)|Apocalypse]] and selected as his [[Horsemen of Apocalypse (Earth-616)|Final Horseman]] '''[[War]]''' in the event that all other plans of Apocalypse failed.{{r|Uncanny X-Force #3}}

===Western Roman Empire (4th century)===
In the 4th century AD, The Roman Empire was divided,{{r|Marvel Atlas #1|; [[Greece]]'s entry}} and its capital moved from Rome to [[Constantinople]],{{r|Marvel Atlas #1|; [[Italy]]'s entry}} in the '''[[Eastern Roman Empire]]''',{{r|Marvel Atlas #1|; [[Greece]]'s entry}} and the western part of the Empire became the '''Western Roman Empire'''.{{r|Marvel Atlas #1|; [[Italy]]'s entry}}

