===5th century===
At the beginning of the 5th century, the Romans retreated from the province.{{r|Marvel Atlas #1|; [[United Kingdom]]'s entry}}

====Fall of the Rome / Romulus Augustus' rule====
===5th century===
[[File:Franks from Doctor Strange, Sorcerer Supreme Vol 1 37 002.jpg|left|250px|thumb|"Fall of Rome"]]
In 451 A.D., [[Attila the Hun (Earth-616)|Attila the Hun]], the ruler of the [[Hunnic Empire]], attempted to invade [[Champagne-Ardenne]] but was thwarted thanks to the assistance of 1940s time traveler [[Thomas Tyme (Earth-616)|Tommy Tyme]] during the [[battle of Chalons]], whose knowledge proved useful to Roman general [[Flavius Aëtius (Earth-616)|Flavius Aëtius]], who drove Attila and his minions back.{{r|Mystic Comics Vol 2 2}}{{citation}}{{Verify source}}<!-- datation, historical events, names of historical places and peoples -->

In 476 A.D., when the last Roman Emperor, [[Romulus Augustulus (Earth-616)|Romulus Augustus]], was deposed, the Western Empire came to end, and fractured into smaller kingdoms.{{r|Marvel Atlas #1|; [[Italy]]'s entry}}{{r|Incredible Hulks Vol 1 627}}

After the fall, the [[Franks]] went on to conquer the land south of the Rhine and make it under their name, by the mountainous "Rock of the Franks", which is the meaning of the word "'''[[Frankenstein Family|Frankenstein]]'''" waited silently, is first of all blurred, Not yet sated. [[Castle Frankenstein]] would one day be built on that site cursing their line for centuries to come. {{r|Doctor Strange, Sorcerer Supreme Vol 1 37}}

===Legacy===
The legacy of the Roman Empire is the set of cultural values, religious beliefs, and the technological and other achievements of Ancient Rome that were passed on after the demise of the empire itself and continued to shape other civilizations, a process which continues to this day.

Over the years, [[Flavius Scollio (Earth-616)|Flavius Scollio]] captured people from the surrounding area to be his subjects, including the [[Fantastic Four (Earth-616)|Fantastic Four]] and [[T'Challa (Earth-616)|Black Panther]] when they arrived to investigate the tower. Flavius fancied the [[Susan Storm (Earth-616)|Invisible Girl]] with the intention of making her his wife but his plan was foiled when she removed the helmet, which destroyed everything he created and reduced Flavius to a pile of bones.{{r|Fantastic Four #241}}
